Canada's 1.20 billion dlr bond offer wasvirtually sold out as bond prices closed weaker in moderatetrading, dealers said.    Sales of today's issue were slowed by the decline inAmerican credit markets and rising oil prices, which stirredconcerns about inflation, the traders said. The issue wasselling at or just below issue price.    Overall prices fell as much as a point, with the benchmarkCanada 9-1/2 pct of 2001 at 106-3/8 5/8, the 8-1/4 pct of 1997at 99 99-1/4 and the 8-1/2 pct of 2011 at 98-1/8 3/8. Reuter&#3;